title: For Sale:  Winchester -- model 1300 Speed Pump 12 gauge shotgun_S1
postcontent:
This auction is for a Winchester model 1300 Speed Pump 12 gauge pump shotgun.  Mechanically this gun functions well and condition is very good.

Type: Pump-action shotgun
Stock & Forend: Black synthetic
Gauge: 12, Chamber  3"
Weight: 6.7 lbs to 7 lbs
Length: 49"
Barrel length: 28"
Capacity: 5 rounds

The Winchester 1300 shotgun was first introduced in around 1981, when the US Repeating Arms Company (USRAC) took over production of the 'Winchester' brand guns from the Olin / Winchester corporation. In fact, the model 1300 was a slightly modified version of the previous Winchester model 1200 shotgun, which was manufactured by Olin /Winchester between 1964 and 1980. With recent (mid-2007) closure of the USRAC factory production of the Winchester model 1300 shotguns, along with other Winchester brand guns, was moved to Winchester Repeating Arms Co; new guns were manufactured by one of the FN Manufacturing Company's subsidaries located in the Morgan, Utah.

The Winchester 1300 shotguns are known as the "Speed Pump", because of the very fast cycling pump-action, which makes these guns popular among both hunters and sport shooters. 

Receiver is produced from a tough, lightweight aluminum alloy.  The bolt locks into the barrel extension using a rotary bolt head with four radial locking lugs. Rounds are fed from a tubular under-barrel magazine, which can be had in a variety of lengths / capacities. Barrels are quick-detachable and fitted with replaceable chokes and a sighting rib.

As with all of our suppressors, we have utilized state-of-the-art mono-core technology to provide you with excellent suppression, minimum number of parts to juggle, (the entire suppressor disassembles into only three parts), minimum poi shift, and unmatched ease of cleaning and user maintenance. title: For Sale:  FS: Used Sig P239 in 9mm, Aluminum Grips, 4 mags
postcontent:
For sale is a well-used, carried, and perfectly functioning Sig Arms/Sig Sauer P239 chambered in 9mm, DA/SA. 

The gun is great shape mechanically, but it does show cosmetic signs of holster wear and use. There are rub marks on the slide, though the black nitron finish is intact, and there is significant rubbing on the exposed portion of the barrel where it makes contact with the slide (as any semi-auto is wont to do). The frame is blued, and has an inky look in the photos, but I find under most lighting conditions the gun is entirely black. This is not the SAS package, nor does the gun have night sights. 

The gun came with Hogue rubber grips with finger grooves. While comfortable at the range, they weren't great for carry, and bulked up the gun, so I bought some black Hogue aluminum grips, with pretty aggressive checkering, to slim things down (and make the entire gun metal). The aluminum grips are mint and fit together perfectly around the back of the gun. I also acquired a couple extra mags during my ownership of this gun, and all four will be included with it. 


Willing to drive a little to make this sale.
